{
  "texts": [
    "For instance, if we adopt the view that normative theories converge more than they disagree, foot_51 a resource-rational algorithmic gametheoretic analysis could help to identify the conditions under which certain theories are more practically viable than others.",
    "E.g., what sort of cognitive abilities and computational resources are required for a certain moral heuristic-e.g.",
    "an action-guiding normative theory-to support the highest possible moral prosperity for a community of agents?",
    "What sort of moral behaviors can be effectively computed or justified, and what behaviors can only be learned?",
    "Ideally, such investigations could not only illuminate the specific resources a computational agent need in order to be morally competent, but explain the very resource-rational rationales that underpin our most prominent ethical theories."
  ]
}